extends _manual.pug

block append title
  | Tune options

block content
  h2 Tune options
  hr

  p Tune options controls how the controller works at a fundamental level, independently from the operative system. The tune options are applied to all profiles, and will be stored in the controller memory even if the controller is powered off.
  p The tune options are configurable by the user directly on the controller:
  ul
    li Hold the #[em Home #[+home]] button.
    li Hold the #[em Directional Hat #[+hat]] either up, down, left or right. Each direction tune a different option (see below).
    li Release the #[em Directional Hat #[+hat]], but keep holding the #[em Home #[+home]] button.
    li Notice how the LEDs are showing which #[em tune option is selected] (represented by a solid light) and its #[em current value] (represented by a blinking light).
    li Change the value up or down by using the #[em scroll wheel up or down].
    li Release the #[em Home #[+home]] button.

